        <descriptionSet>
            <description>Sangorski &amp; Sutcliffe is a prestigious bookbinding firm established by Francis Sangorski (1875-1912) and George Sutcliffe (1878-1943) in London in 1901. Considered to be one of the most important bookbinding companies of the 20th century, they are particularly famous for its jeweled bindings that oftentimes used real gold and precious stones in their book covers.  This poem by Ralph Waldo Emerson has been turned into an elaborately illuminated manuscript, written on parchment in black and red ink.</description>
